  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "TUNNEL SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p><br /></p><p><strong>Site & Construction Supervision</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise tunnelling activities (NATM, TBM, drill & blast, cut-and-cover, etc.)</p></li><li><p>Ensure work follows <strong>approved drawings, method statements, and specifications</strong></p></li><li><p>Coordinate daily work plans and allocate manpower and equipment</p></li><li><p>Monitor excavation, mucking, lining, shotcreting, waterproofing, and backfilling works</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper sequencing of tunnel operations</p></li></ul><p><strong>Health, Safety & Environment (HSE)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Enforce strict compliance with <strong>HSE regulations and site safety plans</strong></p></li><li><p>Conduct toolbox talks and daily safety briefings</p></li><li><p>Identify hazards (gas, water ingress, ground instability) and implement controls</p></li><li><p>Ensure use of PPE and safe work practices at all times</p></li><li><p>Respond immediately to incidents or unsafe conditions</p></li></ul><p><strong>Quality Control</strong></p><ul><li><p>Inspect works to ensure compliance with quality standards</p></li><li><p>Monitor concrete, shotcrete, rock support, and lining quality</p></li><li><p>Ensure correct installation of rock bolts, steel ribs, mesh, and waterproofing systems</p></li><li><p>Report non-conformances and ensure corrective actions</p></li></ul><p><strong>Coordination & Communication</strong></p><ul><li><p>Liaise with site engineers, surveyors, safety officers, and subcontractors</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with TBM operators or blasting teams where applicable</p></li><li><p>Communicate progress, issues, and risks to project management</p></li><li><p>Assist engineers with site measurements, reports, and records</p></li></ul><p><strong>Reporting & Documentation</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain daily progress reports and shift logs</p></li><li><p>Record manpower, equipment usage, and material consumption</p></li><li><p>Report delays, breakdowns, or ground condition changes</p></li><li>Support inspections by consultants and clients</li></ul><p></p><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><p><ul><li>Minimum 5 years of experience in <strong>tunnelling construction</strong></li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Proven experience supervising tunnel works (NATM, TBM, or drill & blast)</li></ul></p><ul><li><p>Familiarity with underground safety standards and procedures</p></li><li><p>Problem-solving abilities</p></li></ul><p><ul><li>Able to perform day or night shifts in underground</li></ul><ul><li>Able working 6 days per week, 12 shifts</li></ul></p>",
